by hanahiroAze at 2016-11-13T06:07:01Z

In `@Route("/", defaults={"page": 1}, name="blog_index")`, the parameter "page" is set as int value by `{"page": 1}`, but in `@Route("/page/{page}", requirements={"page": "[1-9]\d*"}, name="blog_index_paginated")`  the parameter "page" is set as string value by `{"page": "[1-9]\d*"}`.

When I dump `$page` parameter in `BlogController.indecAction()`, Symfony profiler says like below and  I found the parameter's type is different.

- Top page -> application
![2016-11-12 19 21 32](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/9178166/20243966/0566415a-a9b2-11e6-8172-3468cb82cec3.png)

- click "Next" button
![2016-11-12 19 22 58](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/9178166/20243971/1969ad18-a9b2-11e6-91e4-0552f0104692.png)

- click "Previous" button
![2016-11-13 15 03 08](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/9178166/20243974/5e66fbbe-a9b2-11e6-9695-9446af66a220.png)

